\subsection{mzTab-M reliability mapping}{

Reliability levels follow the Metabolomics Standards Initiative (MSI) scale:
\itemize{
\item \strong{1} – confirmed (score ≥ 0.7 with spectral library evidence)
\item \strong{2} – probable (score ≥ 0.5; or spectral match, any score)
\item \strong{3} – putative (score ≥ 0.2)
\item \strong{4} – unambiguous compound class only (everything else)
}
}

\subsection{id_confidence_measure columns}{

Four TIMA-specific confidence measures are exported as
\verb{id_confidence_measure[1..4]} in the MTD section and as additional
columns in the SME section.  All use the \code{TIMA} user-controlled CV
namespace (no PSI-MS accession exists for these composite scores):
\itemize{
\item \verb{[1]} – \code{score_final} (combined TIMA score; \code{TIMA:001})
\item \verb{[2]} – \code{score_biological} (taxonomic score; \code{TIMA:002})
\item \verb{[3]} – \code{score_chemical} (chemical consistency; \code{TIMA:003})
\item \verb{[4]} – \code{candidate_score_similarity} (spectral similarity;
\code{TIMA:004}; omitted when no spectral evidence is present)
}
